      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "content": "A team with real-world modernization experience."
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "content": "Long-time development leader in Haiti who has overseen the effective management and distribution of more than $26 million USD into community-led programs. Under his leadership, over 5,000 women were organized into Self-Help Groups, generating approximately $485,000 USD in community-controlled savings and loans, strengthening local financial independence. His integrated model has supported the planting of 2.9 million trees, protection of 60 million square feet of watershed, and measurable improvements in water access. Nutrition programs engaging 1,600 households contributed to an 82% reduction in infant malnutrition, while education initiatives have impacted 52,000 students across 400 schools. He modernized and vertically integrated salt production, building 11,000 metric tons of annual sea salt capacity with projected revenues of $1.2 million USD per year, creating sustainable local enterprise."
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "content": "Over 10 years of experience in digital transformation across global enterprises and high-risk industries. Deployed a Microsoft Digital Distribution serving 1,900+ institutions worldwide, drove digital transition from paper-based safety programs to ISO-aligned systems at eCompliance (acquired by Alcumus), and led Go-to-Market as Executive Director of Sales at 3motionAI, driving AI-based workplace safety solutions which led to its acquisition by VelocityEHS. Raised over $700,000 USD to support community initiatives in Haiti and the Dominican Republic, identifying critical gaps in technology and financing infrastructure in low-connectivity environments."
      }
    ],
